 Tunisia]]</small><ref name=\"annualmeeting\"/>\n{{flagcountry|Democratic Republic of Armenia}} {{small|(in 1920)}}<br />[[File:Flag of the United Kingdom.svg|border|22px|link=]] [[British Empire]] {{small|([[Occupation of Constantinople#End of the occupation|until 1923]])}}{{Ref label|ddd|d}}\n*<small>[[File:Flag of the United Kingdom.svg|border|22px|link=]] [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]]</small>\n*<small>{{flagcountry|British Raj}}</small><ref>Briton Cooper Busch: ''Mudros to Lausanne: Britain's Frontier in West Asia, 1918-1923'', SUNY Press, 1976, ISBN 0-87395-265-0, [http://books.google.com/books?id=Yz_OVCTNI04C&pg=PA216&dq=indian+troops+turkey+1920&hl=de&sa=X&ei=RdSiT7y2CszSsgbV7onZBw&redir_esc=y#v=snippet&q=%22attitudes%20of%20those%20indian%20troops%20who%20increasingly%20made%20up%22&f=false sayfa 216].</ref><ref>\"[http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9D06E2D6143AEE32A2575BC1A9609C946195D6CF&scp=1&sq=turkey+indian+troops&st=p British Indian troops attacked by Turks; thirty wounded and British officer captured-- Warships' guns drive enemy back],\" ''New York Times'' (18 June 1920).</ref><ref>\"[http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9501E6DF173AEE32A2575BC1A9659C946195D6CF&scp=4&sq=turkey+indian+troops&st=p Allies occupy Constantinople; seize ministries; Turkish and British Indian soldiers killed in a clash at the War Office],\" ''New York Times'' (18 March 1920).</ref> \n<hr>{{nowrap|{{flagcountry|Ottoman Empire|1823}} {{small|([[Abolition of the Ottoman sultanate|until 1922]])}}{{Ref label|eee|e}}}}\n* [[Kuva-yi Inzibatiye]] {{small|(in 1920)}}\n* [[Revolts during the Turkish War of Independence|Royalists]]\n<hr>{{flagicon image|Flag of Georgia (1918\u20131921).svg}} [[Democratic Republic of Georgia|Georgia]] {{small|([[Red Army invasion of Georgia|in 1921]])}}<hr>{{flagcountry|United States|1912}}<br /><small>([[Bombardment of Samsun)]]\n| commander1  = {{nowrap|{{flagdeco|Ottoman Empire|1823}} [[Mustafa K