as Who\" />\n\n===Navy===\n* [[Willoughby Baynes Huddleston|Commander Willoughby Huddleston]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] (1866\u20131953), [[Aide-de-camp|ADC]] to [[John Sinclair, 1st Baron Pentland|Lord Pentland]], [[Governor of Madras]] (1912\u201319)<ref name=\"auto2\"/><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Captain W.B. Huddleston'', 5 May 1953, p.8</ref>\n* [[Thomas Oloff de Wet|Captain Thomas Oloff de Wet]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1869\u20131940), Principal Naval Transport Officer during the [[Occupation of Constantinople|evacuation of Constantinople]] in 1923<ref>A Register of the Old Boys of the [[Bedford Modern School]]. Compiled and Edited by H.E. Vipan.  Published in [[Bedford]] by W.J. Robinson, 1900.  School Honours; p. ix</ref>\n* [[Alfred Ransom (Royal Navy officer)|Rear Admiral Alfred Ransom]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1871\u20131953), First World War naval officer<ref>H.E. Vipan,''A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School'' (Bedford, no date), p. 103</ref>\n* [[Sir Ernest Whiteside Huddleston]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Royal Indian Navy|RIN]] (1874\u20131959), [[Aide-de-camp]] to the [[Governor-General of India|Viceroy of India]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Francis Walter Despard Twigg|Captain Francis Walter Despard Twigg]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1883-1951), senior officer in the Royal Navy<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=13|title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War|website=livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk}}</ref>\n* [[Herbert Roff Newton|Commander Herbert Newton]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] (1900\u20131973), [[Royal Navy]] Commander and [[Deputy Lieutenant]] of [[Bedfordshire]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\" />\n* [[Rear-Admiral Jack Kenneth Highton]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1904\u20131988), [[Aide-de-camp]] to Queen [[Elizabeth II]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Fred Stovin-Bradford|Captain Frederick Stovin-Bradford]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Distinguished Service Cross (United Kingdom)|DSC&Bar]] (1919\u20131974), [[Royal Navy]] Commander ([[Fleet Air Arm]])<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Sir Ted Horlick|Vice-Admiral Sir Ted Horlick]] [[Order of the British Empire|KBE]] (born 1925), Director General of British Ships (1979\u201383), Chief Naval Engineer Officer (1981\u201383)<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\" />\n\n==Industry and commerce==\n[[File:John Howard (1791\u20131878), Mayor of Bedford.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[John Howard (industrialist)|John Howard]]]]\n[[File:Arthur John Carter - Queensland Politician.png|thumb|115px|right|[[Arthur Carter (Queensland politician)|Arthur Carter]]]]\n[[File:George Herbert Farrar01a.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[George Farrar|Sir George Farrar Bt]]]]\n* [[John Howard (Industrialist)|John Howard]] (1791\u20131878), [[Business magnate|industrialist]], inventor of agricultural equipment and four times [[Mayor of Bedford]]<ref name=\"worldcat.org1\">{{Cite book|title=The Harpur Trust, 1552\u20131973.|work=worldcat.org|isbn=9780950291703|year=1973|oclc = 903515}}</ref>\n* [[James Howard (agriculturalist)|James Howard]] (1821\u20131889), industrialist and inventor of agricultural equipment. [[Member of Parliament|MP]] for Bedford<ref name=\"worldcat.org1\"/>\n* [[Frederick Howard (industrialist)|Sir Frederick Howard]] [[Justice of the peace|JP]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] (1828\u20131915), [[Business magnate|industrialist]]<ref name=\"worldcat.org1\"/>\n* [[Charles Wells (brewer)|Captain Charles Wells]] (1842\u20131914), founder of [[Charles Wells Ltd]], [[progenitor]] of the [[Wells baronets]] of [[Felmersham]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://virtual-library.culturalservices.net/webingres/bedfordshire/vlib/0.digitised_resources/bedford_digitisation_charles_wells_brewery.htm|title=charles wells brewery timeline \u2013 Digitised Resources \u2013 The Virtual Library|author=Bedford Borough Council and Central Bedfordshire Council|work=culturalservices.net|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Arthur Carter (Queensland politician)|Hon. Arthur Carter]] (1847\u20131917), businessman, Australian [[Consul (representative)|Consul]] to [[Norway]], [[Members of the Queensland Legislative Council|Member of the Queensland Legislative Council]]<ref>{{Cite book|chapter-url=http://adb.anu.edu.au/biography/carter-arthur-john-5521|title=Biography \u2013 Arthur John Carter \u2013 Australian Dictionary of Biography|work=anu.edu.au|accessdate=30 January 2015|chapter=Carter, Arthur John (1847\u20131917)|publisher=National Centre of Biography, Australian National University}}</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''The Hon. A. J. Carter'', 10 November 1917, p.3</ref>\n* [[Sir George Farrar, 1st Baronet]] (1859\u20131915), mining magnate, politician and soldier<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oxfordindex.oup.com/view/10.1093/oi/authority.20110803095811125|title=Sir George Herbert Farrar|work=oup.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bodley.ox.ac.uk/dept/scwmss/wmss/online/blcas/farrar-george.html|title=Papers of Sir George Farrar and family|work=ox.ac.uk|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Henry Batten Huddleston|Lt. Col. Henry Batten Huddleston]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Volunteer Officers' Decoration|VD]] (1864\u20131944), Chief Agent and later a Director of the Burma Railways<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=12|title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War|website=livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk}}</ref>\n* [[Walter Nutt (businessman)|Hon. Walter Nutt]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1874\u20131940), managing director of [[Straits Trading Company|The Straits Trading Company]] (1918\u201321)<ref>1891 England Census, Boarder at Bedford Modern School</ref>\n* [[Noel Mobbs|Sir Noel Mobbs]] [[Royal Victorian Order|KCVO]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1878\u20131959), founder of [[Slough Estates]] and [[High sheriff]] of [[Buckinghamshire]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[E.E. Blake]] (1879\u20131961), Chairman of [[Eastman Kodak|Kodak UK]]<ref name=\"mocavo.co.uk\"/>\n* [[William Alfred Pickwoad|William Pickwoad]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Royal Society of Arts|FRSA]] (1886\u20131975), prominent in South America's railway industry. Founding director of the [[Central Bank of Bolivia]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/> \n* [[W. T. Godber]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1904\u20131981), authority on agriculture and [[agricultural engineering]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr W.T. Godber'', 24 April 1981, p.14</ref>\n* [[Sir Henry Cecil Johnson]] [[Order of the British Empire|KBE]] (1906\u20131988), chairman of the [[British Railways Board]] (1968\u201371)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Alastair George MacKenzie]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1915\u20131989), prominent figure in [[Southeast Asia|South East Asian]] insurance during the 1960s and 1970s<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=kn4uAQAAIAAJ&q=alastair+george+mackenzie+bedford+modern&dq=alastair+george+mackenzie+bedford+modern|title=Who's who in Malaysia and Guide to Singapore|accessdate=14 November 2015|year=1967}}</ref>\n* [[Francis Coulson]] [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] (1919\u20131998), [[chef]] and hotelier<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/obituaries/obituary-francis-coulson-1148567.html|title=Obituary: Francis Coulson|work=The Independent|accessdate=30 January 2015|date=1998-03-06}}</ref>\n* [[Edward Roy Kent]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1920\u20132009), estate owner and agriculturalist in th