gh]] (born 1971), [[Special advisers (UK government)|special adviser]] to [[New Labour]] (2003\u20132010)<ref>''The Eagle, Magazine of Bedford Modern School''</ref>\n\n===Overseas===\n* [[William Morgan (Australian politician)|Sir William Morgan]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|KCMG]] (1828\u20131883), [[Premier of South Australia]] (1878\u201381)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Leonard Isitt (minister)|Leonard Isitt]] (1855\u20131937), M.P. for the [[New Zealand Liberal Party]] and member of the [[New Zealand Legislative Council]]<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr. L.M. Isitt'', 15 September 1937, p.17</ref><ref>The Eagle Vol. XVI, no. I (March 1926), p. 55</ref>\n* [[Charles Frederick Gale]] (1860\u20131928), senior Australian civil servant, [[Protector of Aborigines|Chief Protector of Aborigines]] in Western Australia<ref>{{Cite book|chapter-url=http://adb.anu.edu.au/biography/gale-charles-frederick-6268|title=Biography \u2013 Charles Frederick Gale \u2013 Australian Dictionary of Biography|work=anu.edu.au|accessdate=10 March 2015|chapter=Gale, Charles Frederick (1860\u20131928)|publisher=National Centre of Biography, Australian National University}}</ref>\n* [[H.G. Graves|Henry George Graves]] [[Royal School of Mines|ARSM]] (1864\u20131929), Controller of [[Patent|Patents and Designs]] in India between 1904 and 1919<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr H.G. Graves'', 7 November 1929, p.19</ref>\n* [[Ernest Wilton|Sir Ernest Colville Collins Wilton]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|KCMG]] (1870\u20131952), President of the Commission for the Government of the [[Saar (League of Nations)|Saar Basin]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Herbert George Billson]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] (1871\u20131938), Chief Conservator of Indian Forests, 1922\u201326<ref>''Who was Who Vol. III, 1929\u20131940'' (London, 1967), p. 111</ref>\n* [[Sir William Pell Barton]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|KCIE]] (1871\u20131956). [[Resident (title)|Resident]