O]] (1872\u20131940), Officer of the [[British Indian Army]]<ref>H.E. Vipan, ''A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School'' (Bedford, no date), p.64</ref>\n* [[George Godfrey Massy Wheeler|Major George Godfrey Massy Wheeler]] [[Victoria Cross|VC]] (1873\u20131915), was a recipient of the [[Victoria Cross]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.roll-of-honour.com/Bedfordshire/BedfordModernSchoolWW1Memorial.html|title=Roll of Honour \u2013 Bedfordshire \u2013 Bedford Modern School \u2013 World War 1|work=roll-of-honour.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Arthur Charles Rothery Nutt|Lieutenant-Colonel Arthur Charles Rothery Nutt]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1873\u20131946), inventor of the [[artillery miniature range]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Charles Foulkes (British Army officer)|Major-General Charles Howard Foulkes]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1875\u20131969), Britain's chief adviser on [[gas warfare]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Herbert Cecil Potter|Brigadier-General Herbert Cecil Potter]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1875\u20131964)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Charles Temple Morris|Colonel Charles Temple Morris]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1876\u20131956), Commander of the 5th Battalion of the [[1st Punjab Regiment]] between 1921 and 1926<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mocavo.com/Whos-Who-Men-and-Women-of-the-Time-1935/107381/2979#2436|title=Whos Who, Men and Women of the Time, 1935|work=Mocavo|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref>\n* [[James Meldrum Knox|Lieutenant-Colonel James Knox]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO&bar]] (1878\u20131918), Battalion Commander, [[Royal Warwickshire Regiment]], 1915\u201318<ref>H.E. Vipan, ''A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School''(Bedford, no date), p. 72</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Lieutenant-Colonel J.M. Knox D.S.O., Royal Warwick Regiment'', 3 October 1918, p.3</ref>\n* [[Herbert Thomas Dobbin|Brigadier-General Herbert Dobbin]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1878\u20131946), [[Colonel-Commandant]], [[Iraq Levies]], the [[Duke of Cornwall's Light Infantry]]<ref>''Who was Who Vol. IV, 1941\u201350'' (London, 1980), p. 319.</ref>\n* [[Arthur Turner (British Army officer)|Brigadier-General Arthur Turner]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1878\u20131952), [[Cricket]]er, [[rugby union]] player and soldier<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/england/content/player/21615.html|title=Arthur Turner|work=Cricinfo|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Wilfrid Stanley Richmond|Colonel Wilfrid Stanley Richmond]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Institution of Civil Engineers|MICE]] (1881\u20131962), Deputy Director of Roads in the [[British Expeditionary Force (World War I)|BEF]] during [[World War I]]<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Colonel W.S. Richmond'', 30 January 1962, p.15</ref><ref>War Honours Won By Old Boys, Bedford Modern School. Published by H.W. Robinson, [[Bedford]], 1931</ref>\n* [[Henry Cecil Prescott|Lieutenant-Colonel Henry Cecil Prescott]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] (1882\u20131960), Inspector of Police in [[Iraq]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Guy Sutton Bocquet|Colonel Guy Sutton Bocquet]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Volunteer Officers' Decoration|VD]] [[Royal Society of Arts|FRSA]] (1882\u20131961), [[Aide-de-camp|ADC]] to the [[Governor-General of India|Viceroy of India]]<ref>School of the Black and Red, A.G. Underwood (2010 edition). Hardback p.288: ''President of the OBM Club'' in 1952</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr. Guy Bocquet'', 21 January 1961, p.8</ref>\n* [[Brigadier Harold Evelyn William Bell Kingsley]] [[Order of the Indian Empire