orton/newsweather/index.cfm?storyid=2702A2DF-5056-A318-A843C332461FEF98|title=TOP AWARDS FOR RAF AEROSPACE MEDICINE DOCTORS|work=mod.uk|accessdate=20 May 2015}}</ref><ref>Aviation, Space, and Environmental Medicine, Vol. 83, No. 7, July 2012</ref>\n\n==Music==\n[[File:Max Richter - 2015 - ATP Festival (cropped).png|thumb|115px|right|[[Max Richter]]]]\n* [[Roland Bocquet]] (1878\u20131956), composer, Professor of Music Theory at [[Dresden Conservatory]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/><ref>''The Eagle'', Magazine of [[Bedford Modern School]], Vol. XXXI(I) No.233, Christmas 1956</ref>\n* [[Richard Capell]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1885\u20131954), [[Music criticism|music critic]] for the ''[[Daily Mail]]'' (1911\u201333) and the ''[[Daily Telegraph]]'' (1933\u201354)<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1093/gmo/9781561592630.article.04820 |year=2001 |last1=Brown |first1=Maurice J.E. |volume=1 |title=Capell, Richard |journal=Grove Music Online }}</ref>\n* [[Cyril Gell]] [[Royal College of Organists|ARCO]] [[LRAM]] [[Guildhall School of Music and Drama|FGSM]] (1909-1994), musician, conductor of the [[BBC Singers]] and former Professor at the [[Guildhall School of Music and Drama|Guildhall School of Music]]<ref>''[[Bedford Modern School]] of the Black and Red''.  By A.G. Underwood, 1980; updated and revised in 2010</ref>\n* [[Derek Scott (music director)|Derek Scott]] (1921\u20132006), composer and music director for film and television (''[[The Muppet Show]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thestage.co.uk/people/obituaries/2006/07/derek-scott/|title=Derek Scott|work=The Stage|accessdate=29 January 2015|date=2006-07-10}}</ref>\n* [[Gordon Langford]] (1930\u20132017), brass band and orchestral music composer, arranger and performer (''[[Return of the Jedi]]'', ''[[Superman II]]'')<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Paul Paviour (composer)|Paul Paviour]] [[Order of Australia|OAM]] (born 1931) is an English composer, organist and conductor based in Australia<ref name=\"Unde